[On Fri 18 Sep 2015, France submitted to the OIE its follow-up report no 1 on the BTV-8 outbreak, reporting 14 new outbreaks in cattle units and 3 on sheep farms. The affected administrative departments are Alier (14 outbreaks), Puy-de-Dome (2), and Creuse (1). See, with interactive map, at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18684.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 17
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 437 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Cattle / 3493 / 42 / 0 / 0 / 0

According to the report, no vaccination was performed prior to the outbreak ("no vaccination" among "measures applied").
Under "Measures to be applied," the following 2 measures are mentioned:
1. Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)
2. Surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone.

Sequencing results of the current BTV-8 strain may help in clarifying if it is the same one which caused the major 2007-2008 epizootic (indicative of a possible residual, unnoticed circulation?) or a new introduction. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3654452,100.]
